This paper focuses on the design and implementation of a new control plane for low-power multi-hop wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the challenges of achieving reliability and efficiency in the control plane, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY).
